# Whitelist, not blacklist: `main` ignores EVERYTHING by default and only tracks
# the libseq tooling listed below. Graph worktrees (their own graphs/* branches,
# each holding a .git pointer git would otherwise flag as an embedded repo) are
# therefore ignored automatically — `libseq add` never has to touch this file.
#
# `/*` is anchored and top-level only, so un-ignoring a directory below is enough
# to track all of its contents.
/*

# ...except the tooling that lives on main:
!/.gitattributes
!/.gitignore
!/.libexclude
!/README.md
!/LICENSE
!/libseq.bat
!/git-hooks/
!/spell/
!/sys/
